Constructor name should be equal to class name.
There are 2 types of constructor
i.Default
ii.Parameterized
Constructors are called during object creation.
Constructors are used for initialization of objects.
Constructors doesnâ€™t have return type not even void, if we define return type for constructors it will act as method.
Every class will have default constructor.
this & super are used.
Also have other type of constructor called Copy Constructor.
Constructors can be overloaded, but cannot be overridden
Constructor chaining - this() is used to call current class constructor, super() is used to call super class constructor
